data.text:
A March 14, 2001 photo from files of retired professor Tatu Vanhanen, father of Finnish Prime Minister Matti Vanhanen in Helsinki. Police in Helsinki said Wednesday Aug. 11, 2004 they will investigate whether alleged racist claims by the Finnish prime minister's father are criminal and fulfill the conditions of slander and possible incitement to racial violence. In a recent interview, retired professor Tatu Vanhanen was quoted as saying that poor living conditions in Africa are the result of a lower IQ of black people. (AP Photo/Lehtikuva, Sari Gustafsson)
